00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:08,905
Here's the thing,  partition selection is one of the most consequential decisions when designing a Kafka-based system.

2
00:00:08,855 --> 00:00:16,723
It affects ordering guarantees, load distribution, scalability, and even failure behavior.

3
00:00:16,723 --> 00:00:24,342
This session covers how Kafka routes messages to partitions and the trade-offs of each approach.

4
00:00:24,342 --> 00:00:30,539
Interviewers have a favorite trap question about How the Default Partitioner Works.

5
00:00:30,539 --> 00:00:34,250
90 percent of candidates fall for it.

6
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:38,131
I will show you the trap and how to avoid it.

